itemStats.description: Used as a foundation for heavy Scavenger tech. A serious cabin for serious survivors. Great tonnage to compensate for low speed.

Used to be mounted on a military rocket—carrying truck. Today its utilized by Scavengers to carry massive cargo.

itemStats.description: This pickup has survived so many modifications that it looks like an armoured car. A multi-purpose cabin. Average speed, high durability.

A retro-styled cabin with a gas tank inside. Utilized by Pestilence for 'medicinal purposes' for several years. Now its a great tool to set the battlefield alight. Has very high speed and low weight. Works best with fire-based weapons.
itemStats.perks: When activated, for 8 sec. increases fire damage of flamethrowers, artillery and 'Tempura” by 40%, flamethrower range by 50%, flame puddle size by 30% and changes the flames colour to green. Charges while moving.

itemStats.description: A tank is a tank even when the world is ashes. High characteristics and comfortable size, but very low speed.

The 'Cerberus' cabin is a survivors best friend. It understands everything, but just cant speak. Guts enemies in melee combat as if it has three maws. Average tonnage and weight limit of this cabin are helped by very high speed.
itemStats.perks: Built-in melee weapon deals continuous damage to enemies in close combat.

itemStats.description: Single—seater cabin equipped with a roll cage. It was designed specifically for closed-wheel racing and was used in prototypes before the accident. Later it was repeatedly reassembled and strengthened.
itemStats.perks: 1. Always increases booster charge by 50% and heating speed by 30%.  2. At speeds above 75 km/h, each active booster increases damage of all weapons: common — 3%, rare — 6%, epic — 11%. Maximum bonus is 125%.

itemStats.description: A light and compact cabin, the creator of which clearly didnt like to attract attention. He also optimized the guidance system for homing rockets which made their attacks more precise and damaging by reducing their flight range. The enhanced barrage from the corner can be an unpleasant surprise for the inattentive survivors.
itemStats.perks: Homing rockets deal 30% more damage and fly 20% faster. However, the lifetime of the projectiles is reduced by 67%, and their maneuverability and target acquisition range are also reduced.

itemStats.description: A good example of using old scrap and a lawnmower to build a cabin suitable for survival in the Wasteland. This cabins low tonnage is offset by high speed.

This is the growling echo of war that will deafen the Wasteland. This is the frenzy of battle that will wipe away the defeated. This is power encased in metal. This is the apocalypse. And you are its horseman. A cabin with very high tonnage and weight limit yet average speed.
itemStats.perks: Charges when enemies are within 115 m from you. Charges faster with more enemies nearby. When activated, boosts weapon reload speed by 50% for 7 seconds.

itemStats.description: A prototype stolen straight from the factory and amateurishly modified a couple of times to take part in illegal races. A versatile cabin with high speed and average values of the other parameters.
itemStats.perks: Charges while moving. When activated, stops the heating of installed weapons and modules for 3 sec.

itemStats.description: Cabin of a military offroad vehicle. The name perfectly matches the appearance. A multipurpose cabin with a low profile.

Once this cabin belonged to a helicopter and climbed high in the sky. lts just as hard to believe, as the fact that TVs kill people. However, all of this is true. Relatively low power is offset by high tonnage and weight limit, as well as above average speed.
itemStats.perks: Weapon damage increases by 1.5% per second while the car is in stealth. The bonus is reset after 5 sec.

itemStats.description: A classic that has lived through dozens of modifications, perfect for surviving tough conditions in style. A small cabin with above average speed. Suitable for quick and maneuverable vehicles.

Strike first. Steal what was stolen. Win while you have the strength. The law of the new world is simple: its either you or them. A relatively powerful yet not the most durable cabin. The low mass allows reaching high speed.
itemStats.perks: The damage of weapons and drones increases while there are enemy vehicles within 25m of you. The maximum 20% bonus is reached over 10 sec.

itemStats.description: These cabins used to be a key attribute in the rituals of the Frost sect. Inside, they maintained sub—zero temperatures and played loud, dramatic music. But if you throw out all the extra bits, there is enough room for armor and additional equipment. An extremely heavy yet incredibly powerful cabin with a very high weight limit and tonnage.
itemStats.perks: Damage of weapons with limited turn angles increased by 15%.

itemStats.description: Despite the somewhat awkward appearance and many patches on the hood, this cabin can pleasantly surprise you. A balanced cabin which combines average speed, average weight limit and high durability.

Built using blueprints from a war hero, who had spent several weeks in the Wasteland and returned in one piece. A medium powerful cabin with high weight limit and tonnage. Perfect for armoured vehicles on mechanical legs.
itemStats.perks: Increases the maximum speed of mechanical legs by 10 km/h.

itemStats.description: This is a former Pony car class model with a sporty design but without a powerful engine in its base package. Stood among Victor Pyrrhus models for a few years until he modified it for modern demands for an old friend. An average cabin with good tonnage.
itemStats.perks: Each launched drone, wheel drone and turret boost the cabins power by 50% and the whole vehicles resistance to damage up to 10%. Stacks up to 3 times.

itemStats.description: A special version of the pickup cabin. Protective coating reduces the drivers chances of growing a third leg by 10%! Average tonnage and weight limit. A balanced cabin to start your adventures in the Wasteland.

A cabin from a high—power supercar. Initially developed by the Lunatics, but turned out to be too hard to produce. Since then, “Torero” has become popular among lone wolves who value not only its characteristics but also the stylish looks. A very fast cabin. Thanks to a couple of innovative features it makes your weapons more accurate.
itemStats.perks: Increases accuracy of all mounted weapons by 20%.

itemStats.description: Several tusks fixed on this cabins front are not only an element of intimidation, but also an unorthodox melee weapon. This cabin sacrifices tonnage for the sake of low weight and very high speed.
itemStats.perks: For every 100 m. covered by the car, the cabins collision damage increases by 100%. Stacks up to 3 times.

itemStats.description: Before the disaster, such beacons were installed on vehicles that accompanied machinery carrying hazardous goods. The housing is made of impact-resistant polycarbonate and blocks UV light.

By combining the stolen technologies of the Dawns Children and the Nomad drones, the Ravens managed to build a fundamentally new defence system. Their invention poses no danger to the enemy, but it quickly detects and neutralises mines and any destructible projectiles. Mine detection radius is up to 30 m.

Want to shoot some targets with a friend, but he keeps driving away? Just couple his vehicle to yours! You and your ally should both install the module 'Contact 2M”, activate it and get the crafts as close together as possible. One module can only be used to attach to a single vehicle.
A V10 from an old military plane. Easily moves a couple of extra tonnes, but its a bird that can never fly. This is a powerful and durable engine with a single drawback — low speed.
itemStats.perks: Increases maximum speed for augers and tracks by 10 km/h.

itemStats.description: An additional power supply unit that can operate in two modes: 1. Reduces plasma emitter charging time by 26%. 2. Increases projectile speed by 30%, maximum and optimal range — by 20%. Only one power supply can be mounted on a vehicle.

It seems that even the hardened knechte appreciate good jokes. Otherwise, how do you explain the creation of this unit? When activated, the squibs located in the module detonate, and all parts attached to the device are disengaged from the car. Does not deal damage.

People have invented similar tracks during their first global war with each other. Now they are used in the current, less global war. Each mounted track reduces the cabin power. The wider and shorter the track base, the less the turning radius.
itemStats.perks: Increased resistance to firearms damage and excellent grip.

itemStats.description: An elegant yet sturdy medieval wheel. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.
An elegant yet sturdy medieval wheel. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

An early prototype of a compact jet engine with vertical takeoff, also known as hover. The first modification that does not explode at high revs. Well, not every time. Each mounted hover reduces cabin power.
itemStats.perks: Hovers above ground. Ignores all bumps and boasts high flip resistance.

itemStats.description: Pneumatic suspension with variable ride height allows the car to operate in two modes. And also perform tricks. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power. 1

For this rapid-fire autocannon, Nomads experimented with aviation—grade cooling systems. They ended up with a weapon thats particularly efficient in high—speed firefights.
itemStats.perks: Weapon heating while firing slows down as your movement speed increases. Maximum heating reduction — 25% at 80 km/h.

itemStats.description: A clever design, assembled by the hand of a nameless craftsman and found who-knows-where by the Ravens.
itemStats.perks: The projectile explodes after several meters and turns into pellets, increasing its effective range.

itemStats.description: A type of guided rocket. For a few seconds after launch, the operator can set the direction of the rocket using a laser designator.
itemStats.perks: For each second of the rockets flight the explosive damage increases by 18%.

itemStats.description: Looks very much like a gun from the very old world, when the knechte were far from roaming the Wastelands highways. It very well may be that there were no highways back then (such savagery!). Ammunition reserves do not change. The clip is reloaded automatically.
itemStats.perks: The final projectile in the clip deals 200% more damage.

itemStats.description: This 76mm tank cannon is one of the most massive weapons from the great war. Now it continues its service aboard the ”Risen”.
itemStats.perks: After a shot, the weapons resistance to all damage types increases by 20% for 3 sec.

itemStats.description: A revolver firing explosive projectiles from a grenade launcher. Augustus Donner, the Knechte leaders right hand man, cherished this unique prototype and used it only for his own needs. But the gun proved itself so well in battle that it went into mass production.
Launches a mobile combat drone on wheels armed with a grenade launcher. Attacks targets within range.
A curious weapon with mines that wont let a single victim elude you. Does not affect trucks and leviathans.
itemStats.perks: Places mines that fire harpoons at enemies in range.

itemStats.description: Places a landmine with a proximity fuze that detonates if there is an enemy within range. The landmines are active for a limited time. One minelayer can place only two mines at the same time.
itemStats.perks: The mine jumps upon detonation which increases the affected area and allows the explosion to hit low—flying objects.

itemStats.description: Deals additional damage while in contact with the target.
itemStats.perks: Increases durability of all mounted Chainsaws by 15%.

itemStats.description: Lunatics claim its their own original “sturdy blunderbuss”. Yet the ”Leech' looks suspiciously familiar... Deadly at close range. Limited firing angle.
itemStats.perks: While cooling down, the weapons resistance to all damage types increases by 15%.

itemStats.description: A course rocket with each shot hitting like a swarm of locusts. There are 2 rockets in each salvo.
itemStats.perks: If both rockets 0f the volley hit the target, increases blast radius of the next volley by 30% for 5 sec.

itemStats.description: Elegant weapon designed by Nomads for personal use only. The Ravens did not agree with this policy and launched its mass production. Combines the speed of autocannon projectiles with the armour-piercing capabilities of course cannons. It is noticeably superior to the latter in compactness. It fires subcalibre 37mm projectiles and is an ideal choice for those who like to destroy parts from a safe distance.

A precision pulse rifle taken over by a Ravager. It is most effective at medium range, it is perfect for survivors who do not give up until the very end and, having encountered difficulties, only become stronger.
itemStats.perks: If all projectiles from the burst hit the target, the last of them will deal increased damage.

itemStats.description: Do you lay awake at night thinking whos the one to flame? The latest not-a-flamethrower 'Remedy” by Waderkvarn will answer this and a million other questions. Sparks will fly! *The offer is active until 22.12.28
itemStats.perks: Heats up parts on hit. They receive up to 100% more damage depending on the amount of accumulated heat.

itemStats.description: Scar AB has always admired what a massive rocket strike can do even to a heavy armoured target. Thats why the Scavenger engineers have been trying to create a rocket weapon based on a grenade launcher for along time. Yes, its shells fly rather slowly and require time to load the burst. But their damage is terrifying. There are 3 rockets in each salvo.
itemStats.perks: Damage from a rocket launcher projectile explosion on your own armoured vehicle is reduced to 50%.

itemStats.description: When gunpowder and explosives are running dry, good old cables, springs and rebars come in handy. Works just as well.
itemStats.perks: The bolts have significant physical impulse.

itemStats.description: Tackler allows to fire with a very high density and is durable enough not to be shot down during cooldown. And thanks to the reduced energy consumption of these machine guns, one can literally cover an armoured car with them.
itemStats.perks: Increased resistance to all types of damage except energy damage. This perk is disabled when shooting.

itemStats.description: This giant was assembled by a nameless craftsman from an old hunting crossbow with reverse shoulders. During its wanderings in the Wasteland the crossbow lost its paint, but the marks of the master are still preserved somewhere. Fires two bolts in burst. Suitable for accurate medium to long range fire.
itemStats.perks: If the first bolt hits the target, the second bolts impulse is significantly increased.

itemStats.description: Low profile and stern exterior that clearly point to its military heritage. A balanced cabin with a single drawback — low speed.
A cabin from the armored bulldozer of army engineering forces. Excellent for both offensive attacks and to deter the enemys onslaught. Incredible power and tonnage are offset by low speed.
itemStats.perks: The blade at the cabins front boasts increased resistance to all damage types except energy damage.

itemStats.description: One of the biggest cabins in the Wasteland. This time size definitely matters. This cabins low speed is offset by the high tonnage and by incredibly high mass limit.
itemStats.perks: Receiving damage temporarily increases the damage you deal. Max. effect — 30% at 1000 damage.

itemStats.perks: Rocket can be controlled in flight.

itemStats.description: Enormous firepower and ability to deal damage from a large distance while hidden in cover are offset by significant recoil, high spread in motion and utter helplessness in melee combat.
itemStats.perks: Explosion leaves a flammable liquid puddle dealing damage to all targets.

itemStats.description: An arms race often becomes the engine of progress. Who would have thought that you could squeeze out additional firepower from a twin autocannon. But it happened. Moreover, Cyclones rate of fire rises while shooting!
itemStats.perks: The longer the weapon fires, the higher its rate of fire.

itemStats.description: Has tremendous recoil, high accuracy and high initial projectile velocity.
itemStats.perks: If the armoured vehicle was stationary for 2 sec., the damage from the next shot will be increased by 30%. Cooldown 12 sec.

itemStats.description: Cabin from a successful prototype of ultramodern special machinery, which has not had time for mass production. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.
itemStats.perks: Mode 1: increases maximum cabin speed by 10% and power by 50%.  Mode 2: accelerates cooling by 15% and weapon reloading by 15%.

itemStats.description: In passive mode, detects invisible enemies and : marks them on the mini—map. When the activation l button is pressed, launches an airborne detector that follows the armoured car. After 3 sec all enemies within a radius of 200 m from the radar become visible. Invisibility detection range up to 200 m. Enemy detection range up to 200 m. Recon data transfer zone radius 200 m. Mine detection radius is up to 30 m.

Wheel for heavy equipment. It survived the apocalypse and is well preserved mainly due to the fact that the Founders are very sensitive to their tech, never use it unnecessarily and conduct regular inspections. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

Support of a multifunctional mobile crane. The model has two switchable operating modes: as a wheel and as a mechanical leg. Each mounted leg reduces cabin power.
itemStats.perks: Speeds up aiming time by 50% depending on the share of “Bigram” among the vehicles chassis.

Once used to be plasma metal cutter for the heaviest construction work. Now its the final argument in the hottest dispute.
itemStats.perks: Penetrable parts only let through 75% of damage from this weapon and receive the remaining damage.

itemStats.description: Thanks to the Founders, the former drilling tool became a dangerous weapon, most efficient at medium and short range.
itemStats.perks: In the final moments of the shot the beam deals 500% more damage.

itemStats.description: The latest of the oldest welding machines, which mankind had time to come up with before the apocalypse, but just felt short of setting it up. A couple of dozen manipulations by an experienced engineer have turned it into a deadly weapon with two firing modes.
itemStats.perks: After a full charge, damage grows over 2 sec up to 175% of the maximum weapon charge. If you dont shoot in this window, the charge resets and the weapon heats up by 100%.

itemStats.description: Previously used to deliver medium-light materials and tools to the upper floors of buildings. Causes trouble for enemies after the disaster.
itemStats.perks: When dealing damage, reduces the enemys cabin power by 6%. The effect lasts 2 sec. and stacks up to 10 times.

itemStats.description: Tachyon was a frighteningly brilliant child. One damp morning, his story began on the porch of the shelter and was forever cut by the thought — you are not good enough to have a family. It grew into an obsession and after many years was embodied in “Nova” — the perfect cabin. But only its creator knows the true value of such perfection. Modules 'Aegis—Prime' last 75% shorter.
itemStats.perks: Creates a protective field at the front, absorbing any damage from fast moving objects and energy streams for 3 sec. The field has a reduced resistance to explosive damage. Cooldown — 20 sec., if the field is destroyed — 6 sec.

itemStats.description: Few people remember the purpose of the intricate channels of this panel, but it still protects perfectly.
Twin blades mate of hi-tech material and capable of cutting through any metal.
A side panel built by Dawns Children. Widely used among the faction thanks to its unique geometry.
Rugged Dawns Children bumper, forming a kind of protective screen for the whole craft thanks to its robust tubular construction.
Few people remember the purpose of the intricate channels of this panel, but it still protects perfectly.

This invention made Tachyon famous among the people of the Wasteland. The young genius was praised, asked for help, almost manipulated. After that, Tachyon disappeared from the radar for a few years and returned as an adult in the Dawns Children. They said he had been kidnapped. But Tachyon himself and his closest friends are denying that version.
itemStats.perks: When the weapon overheats, the first projectile heats parts on hit. The shotgun also becomes heated. This effect is reset after the shot.

itemStats.description: Together with the family, the fire burned something important inside Surtr, but in return it gave him the ability to see. Growing up in the orphanage, he made some close friends, but never got rid of the aching loneliness. The feeling that he shouldnt have existed.
itemStats.perks: When activated, the player and 3 closest allies are invisible on the radar and become immune to the effects of 'Oculus' and 'Verifier” for 11 sec. Cooldown 20 sec.

itemStats.description: Mystical protection or tough armour of a classic automobile? Theres only one way to find out.
Heavyweight Firestarter structural element. Often used in crafts that deliver the members of the faction t0 the coven.

itemStats.perks: If both rockets of the volley hit the target, increases blast radius of the next volley by 12% for 5 sec.

itemStats.description: Before he ended up at the orphanage, Sigurd was an older brother in a big family. He grew up quickly and learned to keep an eye on the younger ones running around. To call them home, Sig would send a radio-controlled helicopter after them. The boy grew up, and the habit remained, but it had changed slightly over time.

itemStats.perks: If there are 2 or more enemies within a 65 m radius, damage dealt by the cannon will increase by 30%.

itemStats.description: Ravagers have an extremely advanced self—preservation programme. So advanced that inside each wheel they create a sophisticated system to protect its contents. And for some reason its much more active at high speeds in the wheels of Lunatics. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.
itemStats.perks: After reaching a speed of 70 km/h, the wheels damage resistance will increase up to 70% at 90 km/h.

itemStats.perks: After reaching a speed of 70 km/h, the wheels damage resistance will increase up to 70% at 90 km/h.

itemStats.description: Caligaris experiments with the Ravagers technology sometimes lead to unexpected results. Not only that the permanent synthetic dweller appeared in the destroyed helicopter hull. It soon turned out that the cockpit can literally vanish into thin air. The Nomads enjoyed this side effect and their invisibility module only made it stronger.
itemStats.perks: 1. If the invisibility module is not installed the cabin performs its function. Active time 5 s, cooldown 23 s.  2. If the invisibility module is installed then the cabin enhances its effect: decloaking occurs with a delay after taken damage.

itemStats.description: The Scavengers had figured out long ago how to make the rockets find their target. Caligari, on the other hand, managed to connect their technology to the Ravagers systems. The modification made a miss an extremely unlikely result. It fires a barrage of 6 precision rockets that explode with a slight delay.
itemStats.perks: Repeatedly locking on target occurs 33% faster. _

itemStats.description: Most of the Syndicates technical achievements were made possible by advanced energy storage systems. For example, this cabin accumulates the energy that is generated while the armoured vehicle is drifting. It directs the excess energy into the weapon.
itemStats.perks: Increases the weapon damage by 20% when armoured vehicle is drifting. Works only with wheels.

itemStats.description: One cannot hide from the Syndicate — a lesson learned quickly in the Valley. The beacon fired by this module will not only constantly broadcast the enemys position on the map, but will also prevent him from using invisibility. Unless an ally destroys it, of course. itemStats.perks: When the beacon is shot down, the modules cooldown is reduced by 30%.

itemStats.description: A high-tech weapon developed by Syndicate engineers. Incredibly accurate and reliable. When fully charged, it deals colossal damage, but consumes a lot of energy. So much so that, as a result of overcharging, it reduces the speed of the armoured vehicle and the guidance of the weapon itself. Hold the trigger to extend the burst. The charging gradually slows the armoured vehicle and the weapons turning speed.
itemStats.perks: If all projectiles of a fully charged weapon hit the enemy, the damage of the next burst will be 125% of the default.

itemStats.description: The Syndicates devices came as an unpleasant surprise to many survivors. With almost no ability to move, they became an easy target, held down by electric cables. Firing a trap doesnt drag the enemy out of invisibility (but its attack does). The amount of ammunition doesnt change. The clip is reloaded automatically.
itemStats.perks: When dealing damage, the trap gradually reduces the power and maximum speed of the enemy armored vehicle.

clearly didn't like to attract attention. He also
optimized the guidance system for homing rockets
which made their attacks more precise and
damaging by reducing their flight range. The
enhanced barrage from the corner can be an
unpleasant surprise for the inattentive survivors.

Homing rockets deal 20% more damage and fly
20% faster. However, the lifetime of the
projectiles is reduced by 67%, and their
maneuverability and target acquisition range
are also reduced.

optimized power supply scheme speeds up
reloading for the weapon mounted on the vehicle.

achieve maximum lethality. For this purpose they
used many experimental developments - in

deformation of tires. It flows into the batteries of
the energy weapons, periodically increasing their
firepower.

wheels receive a charge that increases the
damage of energy weapons by 5% for 5 sec.

weapons.

itemStats.description:
Scavenger vehicles have always been famous for
their durability, but this time the Scar AB's
engineers have truly outdone themselves. Not only
is their new heavy cabin capable of withstanding
continuous enemy fire, but the reinforced welding
points allow the weapons to remain operational for
a longer time.
itemStats.perks:
For each 1000 pts. of armoured vehicle's
durability increases the durability of the
weapons mounted on the cabin by 8%.
Maximum bonus is 25%.

itemStats.description: Boasts great accuracy, ideal for any scope.
itemStats.perks:
Projectiles pierce up to 2 m of any armor with
slight damage reduction

itemStats.description:
One of the newest Syndicate weapons. Its energy
consumption is compensated by high fire rate and
damage. The 'Dragons' often use it for ambushes
and outpost protection. In these cases even a miss
plays into the hands as it fills the battlefield with a
multitude of nearly invisible and explosive spheres.
Launches a volley of S projectiles that explode on
contact with the enemy or after a short timer
expires.
itemStats.perks:
Damage is increased by 15% for each unit of
energy spent on hardware.

itemStats.description:
Places a landmine with a proximity fuze that
detonates if there is an enemy within range.
The landmines are active for a limited time. One
minelayer can place only two mines at the same
time.
itemStats.perks:
The mine jumps upon detonation which
increases the affected area and allows the
explosion to hit low-flying objects.

itemStats.description:
An armored car with an extremely powerful
24-cylinder engine that can blow away everything in
its path: small obstacles, careless raiders, a roof...
A fast and powerful engine for survivors who are
used to being constantly on the move in battle.
itemStats.perks:
Speeds up the rotation of the weapons in
proportion to the armoured vehicle's speed.
Maximum bonus is 100% at 80 km/h.

itemStats.description:
A powerful inline-four with a charger. 'Catch and
punish! If it tries something funny, repeat! Any
questions?' (P. Pete)
The fastest Lunatic engine.
itemStats.perks:
Increases the reverse speed of wheels up to
50% of standard.

itemStats.description:
When building their roving fortresses, the
Scavengers realized that common auto parts were
not enough. This is when the 'Colossus' came to
help- a tank engine with incredible power.
itemStats.perks:
Increases the durability of all movement parts
by 20%.

itemStats.description:
Ballistics, lead, huge damage. Has limited firing
angle.

A construction welder converted to a melee
weapon. After charging, fires a short stream of
high-temperature flame. Burns parts right through.
Requires a reload.

Tackler allows to fire with a very high density and is
durable enough not to be shot down during
cooldown. And thanks to the reduced energy
consumption of these machine guns, one can
literally cover an armoured car with them.
itemStats.perks:
Increased resistance to all types of damage
except energy damage. This perk is disabled
when shooting.

itemStats.description:
Support of a multifunctional mobile crane. The
model has two switchable operating modes: as a
wheel and as a mechanical leg.
Each mounted leg reduces cabin power.
itemStats.perks:
Speeds up aiming time by 30% depending on
the share of 'Bigram' among the vehicle's
movement parts.

itemStats.description:
This is a former Pony car class model with a sporty
design but without a powerful engine in its base
package. Stood among Victor Pyrrhus' models for a
few years until he modified it for modern demands
for an old friend.
An average cabin with good tonnage.
itemStats.perks:
Each launched drone, wheel drone and turret
boost the cabin's power by 35% and the whole
vehicle's resistance to damage up to 10%.
Stacks up to 3 times.

itemStats.description:
A high-tech weapon developed by Syndicate
engineers. Incredibly accurate and reliable. When
fully charged, it deals colossal damage, but
consumes a lot of energy. So much so that, as a
result of overcharging, it reduces the speed of the
armoured vehicle and the guidance of the weapon
itself.
Hold the trigger to extend the burst. The charging
gradually slows the armoured vehicle and the
weapon's turning speed.
itemStats.perks:
If all projectiles of a fully charged weapon hit
the enemy, the damage of the next burst will
be 125% of the default.

itemStats.description:
Tachyon was a frighteningly brilliant child. One
damp morning, his story began on the porch of the
shelter and was forever cut by the thought - you
are not good enough to have a family. It grew into
an obsession and after many years was embodied in
'Nova' - the perfect cabin. But only its creator
knows the true value of such perfection.
Modules 'Aegis-Prime' last 75% shorter.
itemStats.perks:
Creates a protective field at the front,
absorbing any damage from fast moving
objects and energy streams for 3 sec. The field
has a reduced resistance to explosive damage.
Cooldown - 20 sec., if the field is destroyed -
6 sec.

itemStats.description:
Caligari's experiments with the Ravagers'
technology sometimes lead to unexpected results.
Not only that the permanent synthetic dweller
appeared in the destroyed helicopter hull. It soon
turned out that the cockpit can literally vanish into
thin air. The Nomads enjoyed this side effect and
their invisibility module only made it stronger.
itemStats.perks:
1. If the invisibility module is not installed the
cabin performs its function. Active time 5 s,
cooldown 23 s.
2. If the invisibility module is installed then the
cabin enhances its effect: decloaking occurs
with a delay after taken damage.

itemStats.description:
Stickers can be placed on any surface, as well as
rotated and changed in size.

Plastic excavator engine cover reinforced with a
metal frame. The iron grill prevents the engine
from overheating when working in extreme
conditions.

Paint and patterns.
Can colour most parts.

Along time ago these powerful headlights helped
workers delve deep into the ground around the
clock, dispersing the darkness around the wheels
and underneath them. In a world distorted by
crossout, they proved to be equally useful. There
are now many more dangers hiding in the dark.
Mounted on the left side.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation
gain by 4%.

A modernized version of 'Summator'. 'Argument'
was rebuilt by the Founders from an industrial
fastener tool. Its main difference from the younger
model is a powerful electric magnet that allows to
increase the rate of fire and the projectile speed.
itemStats.perks:
Hitting an enemy reduces the reload time until
the next shot by 30%. Each hit also reduces
the time to fully charge the 'Argument' by 5%
up to 4 times.

itemStats.description:
Stickers can be placed on any surface, as well as
rotated and changed in size.

Part of the excavator hull, cut from the corner of
its rear end. The Founders reinforced the part with
a metal frame, but left the slots for the headlights.
There was no point in covering a couple of holes in
the plastic hull with steel.
Mounted on the right side.

Part of the excavator hull, cut from the corner of
its rear end. The Founders reinforced the part with
a metal frame, but left the slots for the headlights.
There was no point in covering a couple of holes in
the plastic hull with steel.
Mounted on the left side.

Industrial equipment of the Founders is famous for
its power and reliability. It was often used in the
field to build trenches and roads, which always
required a large supply of power. The autonomous
combined generator 'Bootstrap' solved this
problem easily.
Explodes when destroyed. Only one generator can

rotated and changed in size.

A yellow plastic hood on a metal frame. It hid the
inside of industrial vehicles from prying eyes. Now
it's used by the Founders.

a Used for one-time production of a part
Another industrial tool once used successfully in
mining. The power of this laser drill was so great
that it could melt rocks. The tech-sawy Founders
didn't have to argue long about what was tougher
- their enemies or the rocks. They easily adapted
the tool for combat conditions. And practice soon
showed that armoured vehicles are seriously
inferior to rocks in terms of durability.
itemStats.perks:
If the beam hits an enemy entirely, at the end
of the shot it additionally heats up the parts
and deals 800% more damage.

Plastic fender from an industrial truck, reinforced
with a metal frame.
Mounted on the left side.

Mounted on the right side.

The front part of the excavator hull. A huge
radiator is inserted into the plastic covering,
reinforced with a metal frame.

a Used for one-time production of a part
Back in the old days, 'Parser' was used to find weak
spots in mountain rock deposits. With a proper
tuning from the Founders, this tool continued to
perform its function, but in the hulls of the
armored vehicles of the family's enemies.
itemStats.perks:
The damage of the next shot is increased by
3% for each shell that hits the enemy.

itemStats.description:
A rear bumper from an underground mining
bulldozer. It's entirely cast from steel, so it can
withstand almost any physical impact. The
Founders were only able to cut it off with a
blowtorch, and afterwards they painted it yellow
again.

Paint and patterns.
Can colour most parts.

Machine gun with extreme rate of fire and a burst
fire mode. Don't expect pinpoint accuracy and huge
damage, but it can provide surprising density of
fire.

Armour-piercing projectiles, ballistics, lead, huge
damage. Has limited aiming angle.
itemStats.perks:
Fires armor-piercing projectiles exploding after
piercing 2 pins of the armored car structure.

itemStats.description:
A curious weapon with mines that won't let a single
victim elude you. The capture lasts 7 sec. and does
not affect trucks and leviathans. The landmine
explodes after 45 sec. One minelayer can place only
two mines at the same time.
itemStats.perks:
Places mines that fire harpoons at enemies in
range.

itemStats.description:
Four-barreled grenade laucnhers of Nomads gained
a fearsome reputation in the Wasteland. Alas, their
high cost didn't allow to establish mass production
for reliable protection of wandering settlements.
Thus, the 'Thresher' was created. A rapid-fire
double-barreled grenade launcher that could
literally 'thresh' the enemy from a safe distance.
And it is much easier to produce.
itemStats.perks:
Hitting the target at a 20 m distance increases
the damage by 7% for 1 sec. Stacks up to 5
times.

itemStats.description:
A vertically-aligned rocket engine provides steady
thrust and lets the vehicle hover above ground.
Each mounted hover reduces cabin power.
Mounting any movement parts other than the legs
reduces the height of the hover flight.
itemStats.perks:
Hovers above ground. Ignores all bumps and
boasts high flip resistance.

itemStats.description:
Allows for precise shots at long range in any
direction.
itemStats.perks:
A direct hit increases the weapon's damage by
20% for 10 sec. Stacks up to 3 times. Resets
when you miss.

itemStats.description:
Previously used to deliver medium-light materials
and tools to the upper floors of buildings. Causes
trouble for enemies after the disaster.
itemStats.perks:
When dealing damage, reduces the enemy's
cabin power by 4%, which reduces speed and
acceleration (not considering the max. speed
of the movement parts). The effect lasts 2
sec. and stacks up to 10 times.

itemStats.description:
According to popular belief, only Nomads can
escape anomalies alive. No surprises here. With the
'Punisher' on their car anyone could.
itemStats.perks:
Successfully landing 40 shots increases
damage by 100% for 6 seconds. Each miss
increases the number of hits required.

itemStats.description:
The Syndicate agents brought weapons that were
previously unseen in the Valley with them. And while
the locals could somewhat understand what drones
and minelayers were, the plasma rocket launcher
'Yokai' proved that any developed technology was
indistinguishable from magic. These rockets with
deadly contents will surely make anyone believe in a
higher power. And even start praying.
itemStats.perks:
If the rocket doesn't hit the enemy, its blast
damage increases by 40% and its blast radius
increases by 100%. The damage doesn't decrease
as you move away from the center of the blast.

itemStats.description:
Enormous firepower and ability to deal damage
from a large distance while hidden in cover are
offset by significant recoil, high spread in motion
and utter helplessness in melee combat.
itemStats.perks:
Explosion leaves a flammable liquid puddle
dealing damage to all targets.

itemStats.description:
An experimental cabin created by the Engineers after
combining their developments with the Ravager
technologies. It has an autonomous repair module that
can patch up parts during combat. But the Engineers
have not yet managed to optimize the cooling system,
which is why the module severely heats up the cabin
when activated.
itemStats.perks:
When the module is activated, the cabin heats up,
and when it's deactivated, the cabin cools down
within 5 sec., restoring up to 10% of the durability
per second to the parts attached to the power
nodes

itemStats.description:
The younger brother of the 'Protector' machine gun. It
was created for base defence. With the 'Guardian',
engineers tried to achieve a high rate of fire and
increased durability for the machine gun to maintain
this rate.
itemStats.perks:
Every successful hit on an enemy increases
resistance to all types of damage by 1%. The
effect is active for 1 sec. and stacks up to 10
times.

itemStats.description:
War has always contributed to the development of
technology. Following the constant enhancement of
the Ravagers, the Valley inhabitants had to improve
themselves as well. Based on the shielding technology
of the enemy, the Engineers managed to create a
module that reinforces the parts attached to it. Who
knows what else this struggle might bring to people.
Only one defence module 'Averter' can be mounted on
a vehicle.
itemStats.perks:
Increases the damage resistance of parts
attached to power nodes up to 30%.

itemStats.description:
A three-barreled rocket launcher with projectiles that
fly in a spiral. One by one, three rockets hit their target,
spinning it in a deadly dance. One-two-three,
one-two-three.
itemStats.perks:
The impulse and blast damage of each following
rocket in the salvo increases by 100% and 25%
accordingly.

itemStats.description:
A batch of small-sized wheels with wear-resistant
rubber and excellent traction were brought to the
'Steel Championship 2051' by the Lunatics as a gift to
the leader of the Scavengers. Collector Scar AB was so
delighted with the wheels and their low suspension so
rare for the Wasteland, that he couldn't stay indebted
and let Paris from Psycho Pete's gang become another
commentator for the tournament.
Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

Experimental development of the Syndicate. lt
decodes the control signals of the enemy drones and
then implements its own commands into them. When
activated, the module blocks the operation of drones
and other autonomous devices within a 80 m. radius
for 4 sec.

Does not affect a vehicle's characteristics, but looks
so cool!
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation
gain by 3%.

Rear wing with multiple planes.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation
gain by 5%.

A light and compact cabin, the creator of which clearly
didn't like to attract attention. He also optimized the
guidance system for homing rockets which made their
attacks more precise and damaging by reducing their
flight range. The enhanced barrage from the corner can
be an unpleasant surprise for the inattentive survivors.
itemStats.perks:
Homing rockets deal 20% more damage and fly
20% faster. However, the lifetime of the
projectiles is reduced by 67%, and their
maneuverability and target acquisition range are
also reduced.

itemStats.description:
Reminds you of the good old days and grandma's
chest. They don't make them like that any more.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation
gain by 4%.

Only the worthy ones are allowed to carry this banner
on their armoured vehicle. Those who have nothing to
do with the championship, but dared to mount it on
the car will have to personally answer to the tough
fans from the Wasteland.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation
gain by 4%.

That rare (and perhaps the only) case when fanatics
who love destruction have created something truly
beautiful. The 'Nidhogg' shotgun has won the hearts
of the Firestarters along time ago. But everything can
be made better by adding a little faith and fire.
itemStats.perks:
If at least half of the pellets hit the enemy, the
next shot will be fired with incendiary projectiles
that heat up the parts on impact. Damage to
these parts increases up to 100% depending on
the heating level.

itemStats.description:
This cabin was created by the space development
center for a shuttle that delivered cargo to orbital
stations. The special development allowed to
accelerate the operation of certain systems during the
landing on Earth. The Dawn's children adapted the
technology to work with weapons.
The cabin also has fairly high mass limit, durability and
tonnage.
itemStats.perks:
Decreases the reloading time of all weapons by
15%, then stacks it and distributes it equally
between all weapons except revolvers. The
distribution cannot speed up the reloading by
more than 40%.

itemStats.description:
A sabotage drone created by Nomads on the basis of
'Yaoguai'. After being launched into the specified area,
the drone hovers in the air and activates its own
invisibility module. When an enemy appears nearby,
'Vulture' clings to its important parts trying to
destroy them and then explodes afterwards.
The drone cannot be disabled remotely. Does not
receive a bonus from parts that boost the reloading of
drones.
itemStats.perks:
The drone deals periodic damage to the part it
has attached itself to.

itemStats.description:
Simplified in production, but a no less dangerous
version of the 'Joule' autocannon. The weapon was
designed for medium-close range combat, which
increases its fire rate. Nomads proudly call 'AC62
Therm' a machine gun from the autocannon world.

As soon as the Firestarters invented 'Ripper', their
lives were divided into 'before' and 'after'. Shooting
circular saw blades proved to be not only efficient, but
also fun. That's why those, who have the best
'Rippers', are often the same people who killed the
previous owners of the weapon.
itemStats.perks:
Disks get temporarily stuck in environmental
objects and deal increased collision damage.

itemStats.description:
In pursuit of combat power, Steppenwolf engineers
have even attempted to redesign their flares. They
managed to increase the heating power of the
projectiles, and thus the 'Trombone' auxiliary rocket
launcher entered service.
'Trombone' fires a burst of three high-precision
rockets, which do little damage to enemies, but greatly
heat up the parts within the blast radius.
itemStats.perks:
The longer the rockets are in flight, the better
their maneuverability gets.

itemStats.description:
The most reliable cabin for work in permafrost zones.
The worse the conditions in which 'Ermak' operates,
the better it adapts to them.
A reliable warm hull and a large power supply - it has
everything you need to survive in the far North, but it
will be a great choice for the Valley conditions too.
itemStats.perks:
Upon receiving damage increases the armoured
vehicle's damage resistance by 10% for 7 sec. The
effect stacks up to 3 times. Delay of the effect
boost is 0.4 sec.

itemStats.description:
Dalis Rhyme has proved to survivors that he is a real
scientist when he brought his pulse accelerator to the
Valley. But the inventor has equipped the weapon with
over excessive capacitors that can store more energy
than is needed for a shot. It will definitely increase the
damage, but the excessive energy will be discharged
directly to the driver's armoured car. For survivors,
however, this feature of 'Astreaus' have become just
another reason to respect Dalis even more.
itemStats.perks:
Charging the weapon increases its damage for 0.5
sec. An overcharged shot deals 50% more damage
from the maximum charge, while also distributing
50 pts. of damage to the parts on which the
weapon is mounted on.

itemStats.description:
One would think that a weapon found in a swamp
would unlikely be in a good condition. But the metal
under the dirt was completely unaffected by corrosion
and, once greased, 'Varun' began to shoot faster than
any crossbow Alva had ever seen. However, years of
abandonment have made some adjustments to the
weapon's mechanism: after charging, the bowstring
tension gradually loosens.
itemStats.perks:
For a short time after charging, a shot from
'Varun' deals 20% more damage, while also
having its projectile speed increased by 35% and
the impulse by 50%. If the rate of fire is
maintained, the bonus stacks up to 3 times.

itemStats.description:
For many years Alva wandered through impassable
forests and swamps in attempts to temper her spirit.
And every time the tree branches were entwined into a
wall in front of her and the swamp seemed endless, a
voice in her head urged her to keep going. As a reward
for her persistence, the girl was given an armoured car,
which proved that every obstacle in the way is merely
an excuse to move faster towards her goal.
itemStats.perks:
When the armoured car takes damage, the
'Sabbath' wheel increases the vehicle's power and
maximum speed by 15% and 3% respectively for 2
sec. The bonus is not affected by the amount of
such wheels, but decreases proportionally if there
are other movement parts mounted. Stacks up to
5 times with a delay of 0.3 sec.

itemStats.description:
In 2027, the virus has turned the lives of many people
into hell. But there were also those, who were grateful
to the universe for this apocalypse. The wheel of life
made another turn: the cruelty and aggression, that
were condemned in the old world, allowed those
people to become kings rather than outcasts. And, of
course, that had to be celebrated.

Alva genuinely believes that an ancient raven spirit,
Kutkh, lives inside her armoured car. Every time she
defeats an enemy, it spreads its wings, consuming the
soul of the opponent.

One day a group of raiders found an old videotape in a
shed near an abandoned well. Upon finding a projector,
they gathered in front of the screen, but what they
saw evoked only one desire - to get rid of the
videotape as soon as possible. To the raiders' dismay,
soon after, rumors about the sinister tape began to
spread from all corners of the Valley.

When there is no more hope around, you can only find it

Nothing can change the human nature. And even when
the majority of the Earth's population has perished,
those who remain are eager to show that they are
better than others. It was such fancy men who
invented the retractable headlight 'Eye socket'. Of
course, they explained its mechanics by its usefulness
in combat, but we can see how cool it looks.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation

Dalis Rhyme could never really explain why he loves the
North. And no one could understand him unless they
had been there. But, being a scientist, Dalis figured out
a way to take the North with him.
Does not stop the blast wave. Increases reputation

A rear-view mirror from a research rover. It has a fog

weather conditions.
Mounted on the left side.

with red eyes were actually evil spirits that brought
misfortune. But this information only gave the girl a
reason to look at the birds more closely, as the spirits
evoked more sympathy in her than the shamans of the
Firestarters.
